🌿 What the App Does
Fern AI is an AI-powered mobile app that audits hospital bills for fraud and overcharges. The user photographs or uploads a hospital bill. The system extracts every CPT code and line-item price, validates them against CMS data, flags incorrect or fraudulent charges, calculates total savings, and generates a formal dispute letter.
User Flow:

 User opens app → taps Scan Bill (camera) or Upload PDF
 Image or PDF is sent to FastAPI backend as base64
 Four AI agents run in sequence: Parser → CPT Validator → Price Auditor → Letter Gen
 Results screen shows flagged line items (green = ok, red = flagged) + total savings
 Letter screen lets user copy or share the dispute letter


✅ Core Functionalities
📥 Bill Ingestion

 Camera capture using expo-camera — sends image as base64 to backend
 PDF upload using expo-document-picker — sends PDF as base64 to backend
 Gallery upload fallback using expo-image-picker
 Loading state during upload with progress indicator

🤖 Parser Agent (agents/parser.py)

 Accept base64 image or PDF from FastAPI endpoint
 Call Gemini Vision (gemini-2.0-flash) with structured extraction prompt
 Return BillJSON with all line items, CPT codes, and prices extracted
 Handle multi-page PDFs and low-quality photos gracefully

🔍 CPT Validator Agent (agents/validator.py)

 Load CMS CPT code database into ChromaDB via rag/ingest.py
 For each line item, run RAG query to verify CPT code exists and matches description
 Set flagged: true and populate flag_reason if code is invalid or mismatched
 Return updated BillJSON

💰 Price Auditor Agent (agents/price_auditor.py)

 Compare each line item's billed_price against CMS/Medicare fee schedule
 Flag items where billed price exceeds CMS rate by >20%
 Calculate savings per line item and total_recoverable for the full bill
 Run Isolation Forest (ml/anomaly.py) to catch statistically unusual charge patterns
 Return updated BillJSON

📝 Letter Generation Agent (agents/letter_gen.py)

 Accept final BillJSON with all flags set as input
 Prompt Gemini to write a formal, professional dispute letter
 Letter must include: patient info, provider, date of service, itemized disputed charges, CMS rates cited, and a clear demand
 Return letter as plain text string

🗃️ RAG System (rag/)

 ingest.py — parse cpt_codes.csv and chargemaster files → embed with all-MiniLM-L6-v2 → store in ChromaDB
 retriever.py — semantic search interface used by validator and price auditor agents
 ChromaDB persisted locally during hackathon

🌐 API Endpoints (backend/main.py)

 POST /analyze — accepts { image_base64, file_type }, runs full agent pipeline, returns BillJSON + letter
 GET /health — simple health check
 CORS configured for Expo dev client
 ngrok tunnel setup documented in README


